- download git from gitforwindows.org
- open installer 
- agree to license
- select destination location
- select components (make sure Git Bash Here is selected), the rest are left as default
- keep hitting next for default

- in VS Code, open new terminal
- click on plus sign and select Git Bash
- see $ in the terminal
- in command palette, select Git Bash, 

- cd Desktop
- mkdir Story
- cd Story
- touch chapter1.txt
write smt inside txt file
- git init
to track changes, add file to staging area
- git add .
- git status
- git commit -m 'comment'
- git log 
working dir is where initialize git

- git diff chapter1.txt
roll back to last version
- git checkout chapter1.txt



